  {
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "@ThibautGery This would be on the same website than instantsearch.js, not a new website.\n\nIt's hard to combine on the same page both the API documentation and advanced guides. And we do not want to put advanced guides on Algolia.com even if that's currently the case for some of them.\n\nAt some point instantsearch.js has became a subproduct and thus we need to put most of the documentation on the same website.\n\nHaving the instantsearch website with:\n- homepage\n- documentation\n- guides\n\nis a common pattern for tech projects so it should not be an issue? Or would you really prefer to have a single documentation page with everything inlined?\n",
